summary:
As an engineer with experience in tendering process, I seek to deliver strategies supported by
technical, economic, and risk analysis, offering stakeholders the comfort of knowing that strong strategies and winning proposals are being implemented, while revenue increases. Delivering successful proposals in a competitive international environment drives my professional career.  

Master in industrial asset management, with practice in tendering processes of complex assets holding experience within the Business Unit Wind at Heerema Marine Contractors (The NL), 3.5 years involved in tendering process from the operator perspective at Ecopetrol - Oil and Gas (Colombia), 1 year in the chemical industry, and international experience in Norway, Australia, The Netherlands, and Colombia. 

Some of the stakeholders - Ministry of Infrastructure and Water Management of the Netherlands, the Delft University of Technology, Ecopetrol, Invesa, and the National University of Colombia. Studies in The Netherlands, Norway, and Australia towards engineering and management of complex projects with multiple stakeholders.
